    "answerIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "NSAIDs should be avoided in CKD due to risk of further nephrotoxicity and bleeding interaction with anticoagulation; apixaban dosing follows standard reduction criteria (age ≥80, weight ≤60 kg, creatinine ≥1.5), not eGFR alone."
