    "explanation": "DIC is driven by the underlying trigger (sepsis); treating that cause plus replacing consumed factors (FFP) and fibrinogen (cryoprecipitate) is key, not vitamin K (not a factor deficiency from synthesis failure) or plasmapheresis (used for TTP, not DIC)."
