    "answerIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Erythrasma, caused by Corynebacterium minutissimum, produces coral-red fluorescence under Wood's lamp (from coproporphyrin III), distinguishing it from tinea cruris and candidiasis, which do not fluoresce this way."
