    "system": "Dermatology",
    "topic": "Hereditary angioedema treatment",
    "stem": "A 20-year-old man has recurrent, non-pruritic swelling episodes of the lips, hands, and abdomen without urticaria, unresponsive to antihistamines. Testing reveals low C1 esterase inhibitor levels. What is the most appropriate prophylactic treatment?",
