    "system": "Dermatology",
    "topic": "McCune-Albright syndrome",
    "stem": "A 6-year-old girl presents with vaginal bleeding, large irregular cafe-au-lait macules with jagged borders described as 'coast of Maine,' and a lucent bone lesion consistent with fibrous dysplasia. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
